import.name: Colligus
import.description:
Generally considered a continent lost to the wilds, many Wayfarers travel to this continent in search of an independent life.

However, the continent is not without its dangers, and pieces of people seem about as common as actual people.
import.label: Colligus

import.name: Ascaqua
import.description:
A coastal town that serves as a military research base, but only recently. This small town used to be much smaller and served for some trade to Draconia by way of merchants who manage to trade with Nautregno and Draconia.

However, the coast line and the low wildlife activity in the area made it ideal for nobles to create summer get away homes, quickly followed by the military to keep the nobeles safe.
import.label: Ascaqua

import.name: Alucavous Esplanade
import.description:
This level park resides outside the Church Caelillt.

Constructed by the church's servants, the land is considered holy by the citizens.
import.note:
alucinor (Dream:Common)
pravus (Evil:Common)

The land is actually desecrated but masked by strong magic (DC:30 to perceive, DC:30 for non-religion, DC:25 for religious).

While seemingly safe, many of the church's servants kidnap and kill innocents here as sacrifice to Cthulu to keep his blessings.
import.label: Alucavous Esplanade

import.name: Church Caelillt
import.description:
The church has a long history of being haunted but has always been Caelillt.

And while the air always seems uneasy, the city formed around this temple, and the Alucavous Esplanade was constructed by the servant within Caelillt.

They serve Zeus, and lightning adorns many of the signs.
import.note:
The origin of the name is not known, but the temple has a history of seeming haunted.

+ caeli (Air:Common)
+ illt (Evil:Dwarven)

The church actually serves Cthulu, but they use Zeus as a cover.

No worshippers of Zeus have stayed and survived, their alignment making them keen on something being wrong and the worship to the wrong god angering Cthulu himself. Also, Zeus' chaotic nature serves to hide the more evil and illicit activities of the temple.

This manifests as disappearances and an unusually high murder and crime rate for a city in Draconia that many dismiss as part of its isolationism (thus the smaller dock in the city)
import.label: Church Caelillt

import.name: Risinsini
import.note:
The Devil's Smile
(Elven)
import.label: Risinsini

import.name: Usihaf
import.description: Originally thought to be an ocean when found, it kept its name after being discovered to merely be a lake.
import.label: Usihaf

Temple of the Magic Owl

Trains people in mastery of arcana.
import.note:
òliba (Owl:Draconic)
ilumbo (Magic:Elven)
import.label: Òlibailumbo

import.name: Neulus Re
import.description:
Founded by Rele Mura to help feed the empire of Draconia and ensure that there is enough food for all the people of the Empire and not just the larger cities. 

Created only recently, a small troop helped carve out and now defends the city that is beset on almost all sides by wild beasts that seek to eat the townsfolk. But despite this struggle, the town manages to survive and bring in trade to help sustain life.
import.label: Neulus Re

import.name: Anongo's Smithing and Tools
import.description:
The main blacksmith of Ascaqua, it is a decent smithery and generally has a few assistants or students around to help Stinta around the forge and with general sales and shipping.

Known for their staves.
import.label: Anongo's Smithing and Tools

Sam, Gabi, Franky, Travis, Mike

import.description: A large general store in town
import.label: General Bloody Wares

import.description: The Hungsungar Quarter is a special district in Simer devoted to studying the beasts in the area and the magic that seems to be effecting the area.
import.note: Hugsa (Think:Dwarven)
import.label: The Hungsungar Quarter

import.name: Allu's Smithing Works
import.description: A one woman show, she keeps her smithery running all day and all night, keeping odd hours of business, but known for her quality.
import.label: Allu's Smithing Works

import.description: A large potion shop in the city.
import.label: Lisola's Bottles and Bygones

Ma Uma's Tap is the local bar.

Due to rough trade routes, beer drinks are pretty expensive, but Simer likes to drink.
import.label: Ma Uma's Tap

import.name: Usheel's Usables
import.description: An arcana shop loosely affiliated with the arcane society and run by Usheel
import.label: Usheel's Usables

import.name: Terdorolu
import.description:
An old dock town with a reputation for haunted houses and ghost sightings.

Has since been destroyed and is over-run with ${Fire Elements}$ at last knowledge
import.label: Terdorolu

import.name: Bantiacer
import.description:
The northernmost city of Leoterra. While Cold, is home to a small population of people and is recognized as a city.

While not a port city, there are places along the coast to station a boat and paths to reach the city.
import.label: Bantiacer

import.name: Montis
import.description:
The capital of Leoterra, Montis is a large port city bustling with traffic. The bay of Montis is commonly full with trade ships and markets.

Though while it is the capital, the city has no castle or easily discernible center of rule. However you know the docks contain buildings in which councils make decisions regarding the nation.

Additionally a cluster of large administrative buildings slightly south serve as informational and organization centers for the nation.
import.label: Montis

import.name: No Coelevo
import.description: Originally a military city serving to defend the Bay of Montis, it has grown with extra trade and goods from the near=by coast.
import.label: No Coelevo

import.name: Rica Nix
import.description:
A fishing city on the lake of Usihaf. It maintains the delicate ecosystem of Usihaf and is known for its fish dishes.

Though the delicacies are not without their costs.
import.label: Rica Nix

import.name: Fimus
import.description:
An unwalled city somewhat subject to the wilds. The wild life occasionally poses a problem, wandering the streets, but the people have generally managed, leading to a slightly more rugged and experienced populace than most places.

The castle for its part does allow people inside its walls during dire nights and there are some signs of wall construction attempting to start around the edges of the city, though very far from completion.
import.label: Fimus

import.name: Flucris
import.description:
The river of Flucris is string and plentiful in freshwater, filtered by the natural rocks at the mouth.

Mills use the water to create a large store of grain, though the city has no local farms, leaving a large market for grain trade.
import.label: Flucris

import.description:
The lake Naka is overlooked by the city Oblidiumba.

While a city of Draconia, the citizens here are a bit more independent, not particularly reporting to the Draconian government, though agreeing to stay in good terms with the rest of the continent and participating in trade.

import.name: The Stumble Inn (dep)
import.description: A simple inn managed to remain intact after the disturbance with the fire plane.
import.label: The Stumble Inn (dep)

import.name: Lake Usihaf
import.description:
Usihaf is the water remnants of a once larger lake, possibly joined with the ocean. The history only reveals itself with the life present in the lake despite the lack of a connection to the ocean.

Exploration has shown the lake to have a completely solid bottom but be inhabited by several large water worms that Leoterrians protect and keep fed, resulting in a delicate ecosystem in the lake and the fisheries of Rica Nix.
import.label: Lake Usihaf

import.name: Tebit
import.description: Home to the Arcane Society, primarily a bastion for research to magical beasts in the area and importing some from afar. However, the cold of the northern temperatures makes life hard here, particularly for some of the creatures that have been imported for research.
import.label: Tebit

import.note: Door checker Puzzle: 2 red & 2 blue

import.name: The Great Fire Wyrm Insera
import.description: Insera is a large Wyrm, worshiped by the Kintari. She is known to breath fire as well as being able to travel vast distances.

Having brought peace to many souls suffering in unrest, this shrine ripples with powerful divine energy.

On the outskirts of the bog resides the Esclau Commune, led by Matriarch Evien.
import.label: Isomere Bog

import.name: Imperial Library
import.description:
The primary collection of the knowledge of Draconia, it is the 3rd largest library in the world;
1. Librious Arcanous (Arcane Society, Tebit)
2. The Cortex (Coneixager, Indium)
3. Imperial Library (Draconia, Dranous)

While not the biggest, it is the sole location of some priceless books and knowledge not held anywhere else in the world. Several dozen enchantments protect the building and its books. This in combination with the Draconian Army in the city is why many consider it the most secure library in the world and it has several precious books that it holds for collectors as well.
import.label: Imperial Library

import.name: Dranous
import.description: The City of Dranous is the capital of Draconia. Its port serves the military, the public, and private organizations.
import.label: Dranous

import.name: Night Attack
import.description: 4 guards and some 30 civilians were taken from here over night.
import.label: Night Attack

Giving other things results in angered behavior but gold is also accepted as something like a bank.

import.label: Obhele

import.label: Crawl Space

import.note: Thunder and Storms around this temple as its knowledge swells.
import.label: Temple of Whaitiri

import.label: Venae Haus

Blacksmith open to the public. Good for general repairs and materials.

Has some enchanting available.
import.label: Smida Ingus Grava

import.description: Giant Whirlpool with thunderstorms overhead.
import.note:
Result of a giant magical event in the Sumaku sea.

Consumed Draconia's Fifth Fleet
+ This greatly Weakened dracoina, leading to Nautrengo questioning some of the peace
+ Created by 

Occurred on Dormevum 15, 318
import.label: Giant Whirlpool

import.name: General Goods of Intis
import.description: General Goods Store. Quaint and simple, but has useful goods for the area.
import.label: General Goods of Intis

import.name: Picio
import.description: The city of Picio is a Holy city to the God Serinal. However it has only been so for the last few decades. Prior to that, the city served as a major port city for trade with Nautregno and exploration of the nearby seas.
import.label: Picio

import.name: Public Library
import.description:
Collection of fictional works available to the public.

No return policy, but the collection of books is quite large and well looked after.
import.label: Public Library

import.name: Infernal Plains
import.description:
Demons and ghouls dwell and heal here, never truly leaving the planes of existence, this is where those whose pacts have turned come to finish there eternity.

Filled with lava and fire, its guests are hardy and short tempered. Some live down here in the pain and suffering, some seek to escape to the higher realms in service of the lords within.
import.label: Infernal Plains

import.name: Infernal Citadel
import.description:
The "central" city of the ${Infernal Plains}$. It houses several thousand demons and ghouls in large mountains turned to buildings with various jagged constructs between.

A make shift life exists here where those damned here stay and occasionally have visitors from the other realms.
import.label: Infernal Citadel

import.name: King's Crypt
import.description:
Location of the Squid demi-god Vonaris.

The sea here is saturated by octopi that can cause rough seas.
import.note:
Protected by Vonaris, is a portal to an ethereal realm where very powerful spirits lay in rest and the pressence of living creatures disturbs them.

The ${"content":"Pommel","class":"rs-darkorange"}$ lays in the ethereal realm, the core of the blades power coming from that piece.
import.label: King's Crypt

import.name: Cotens
import.description:
A military city of Leoterra serving the northern area of the continent. Defending against wild beasts more than invaders.

The city also serves as the mainland contact to Tebit, heavily supporting the ${Arcane Society}$.
import.note: Not under the influence of the Arcanous Syndicate, is actively resistant to it due to consecrated grounds to defend against near by malignant crypts. They are unaware of the syndicate though.
import.label: Cotens

import.name: Abandoned Mining Outpost
import.description:
Abandoned campsite from the Draconian empire for mining magical stones.

It was abandoned after being overrun by creatures of the island.
import.label: Abandoned Mining Outpost

import.name: The Library of Curell
import.description:
The library of ${Curell}$ lies here.

Access is restricted to only approved viewers though librarians sit at the front and can help with some information.
import.note: Access requires the approval of 5 of the 9 meisters and they are very picky about who has access.
import.label: The Library of Curell

import.name: Last Seen: The Sepultura
import.description: This is the last known location of The Sepultura for ICP.
import.note: Cardinal's Entry
import.label: Last Seen: The Sepultura

import.name: Neslops
import.description:
A political city in Nautregno, many international negotiations are known to happen here.

Deep in the Orc's territory, visitors are allowed to bring weapons to help them feel at ease.

To this day, only 48 dignitaries have been killed here, of the known 200ish to have come.
import.note:
Currently hosting the Curell Dignataries for war negotiation:
+ Unkulevum 10, 317 - Alucevum 1, 319
import.label: Neslops

import.name: Dens
import.description:
A medium sized city known for having a large number of noble homes as it is a convenient place to get to and from ${Coneixager}$.

This also leads to the ${Sumaku Sea}$ has lead to some war vessels looking to catch important diplomats being present as well.
import.label: Dens

import.name: Qua Silverborn's Last Stand
import.description: Chased down by assassins from hiding in ${Intis}$, he laid dead inside a cave.
import.note:
Left a journal in ${"content":"Intis","class":"rs-darkorange"}$ with a formula for a bomb that could render a ${"content":"Soul Stone","class":"rs-darkorange"}$ inert.

As of Borgevum 15, 319, Qua's body is removed and the following day melted by lava from a thief. Norwind saving his hand for a possible resurrection spell.
import.label: Qua Silverborn's Last Stand

import.name: Racual
import.description:
The ${Draconian}$ diplomatic city.

The land here is considered to be under the sovereignty of the Draconian empire and a similar state exists for her sister cities ${Recatlpo}$ (Leoterra).
import.label: Racual

import.name: Intis
import.description: A small, remote, and desolate city, the few who are here live with purpose, usually research. Very few shops exist and most get there goods directly through imports.
import.label: Intis

The only topical thing of interest seems to be a very deep well.

Run by ${Ixa Saela}$, a good place for a drink and possible some entertainment.

While a larger building, it holds 2 small shrines to ${Dionysus}$ inside.

import.name: Ancient Accuio Aquarium
import.description:
An underground ancient research area that served as an aquarium. Here it seems the ancients researched the optics of underwater vision and the effects of water and evolution, using it to hone arcane magics and enchantments.

Having explored it on ${318 Dormevum 24}$</sub>, you've learned this lab resides several thousand studs underground, and that a shaft protected by a yellow barrier field is the only seeming entrance. Once there it has 4 rooms:
+ A main room seemingly for conducting research and experiments.
+ A room to the north that held an ${Arcanic Channeling Staff}$ after the display panels were turned white by touching both with red, green, and blue power crystals and expending a red crystal to a red glowing panel in the laboratory.
+ A room to the east that holds a pure black box that omits no light and seems to pull at near by power crystals. The lone glass pane floating in the room seems to prompt to do something with a power crystal, responding to red, green, and blue crystals with an intricate arcane sigils in a very complex arcane circle.
+ A room to west that has several floating glass panes that various combinations of power crystals resulted in an alarm, that, after everyone left every room, resulted in the lab going into some form of lock down.

More exploration seems needed, but several power crystals were consumed during the exploration, so more should be acquired before returning, particularly of the red and green variety as those were the colors consumed. Others may be needed as well.
import.label: Ancient Accuio Aquarium

import.description:
Recognizing the density of fish living in lake ${Peilac}$ sent a large army to secure a city on the coast for procuring fish.

The city is constantly beset by beasts, but not out of hunger but fighting for territory, as such the beasts attacking tend to be larger the usual in size, leading the city to have large defenses.

If exploring around the city, officials recommended running away as in the case of larger creatures as they can be very territorial. If attacked, usually you simply need to get out of their territory.
import.label: Simer

import.name: Stjornu
import.description:
The realm of the lingering souls, ${Reykurax}$.

The city resides in what is considered the middle of the sole known landmass where the souls of the dead linger in a lost ethereal form, but they usual avoid the mountains where the mist seems to fall from.

${Stjornu}$ sits in the mountains and has several roads that lead out through the mountain passes around it.

And while the realm can be explored, there is nothing considered to be of note out in the mist.
import.label: Stjornu

The local Inn. Many locals simply live here as well.

Known for providing simple foods and worth to any who pass through.
import.note:
She's just a kind Elf using her inheritted wealth to help people.

She is technically running away from a previous life as a Noble in Coniexager. Ran away to intis for the seclusion but doesn't try to hide from anyone there.

import.name: The Petixnia
import.description:
Location for arena fights in the city of ${Tertiusa}$

There are 2 types of arena fights inside; The public cage fights on the 1st and 2nd floors, and the group death-matches underground.

The public cage fights are fist-to-fist with 10 ranks that vary in payout based on who's entering and how well they're known, but follow a general baseline:
+ Rank 1: Easy Judging Match, up to 10%
+ Rank 2: 10% Payout
+ Rank 3: 20% Payout
+ Rank 4: 30% Payout
+ Rank 5: 40% Payout
+ Rank 6: 50% Payout
+ Rank 7: 60% Payout
+ Rank 8: 80% Payout
+ Rank 9: 200% Payout
+ Rank 10: 600% Payout

The Group death matches are only visible to a few and those willing to risk grave bodily harm and _most_ survive, though not all as some methods of death overwhelm the ${Crystalline Life Preservation Fields}$ present and  the known methods are forbidden in the arena, such as ${Disintigration}$.

Known to be frequented by mercenaries and sailors alike, this can be a good place to easily make a name for ones self and get some crew. They'll still have to be paid of course, in some way or another.
import.note: A Shrine to Odynia helps power the crystal formation in the basement.
import.label: The Petixnia

An old city, not much is known about it. The wild beasts of Sulendirida make it difficult to explore and there's still much that is believed to reside here.
import.label: Hwand

import.name: Plains of Reflection
import.description:
A peaceful area where souls seem to sit and meditate.

Entering the area seems to have some healing properties for the living, but the full extend is not known and sleeping here seems to also magnify the disorientation experienced when waking up, increasing the potential damage taken when resting here.

The area is overseen by a Dwarven spirit named ${Volin Aein}$ who seems to have the ability to communicate more freely with the living but no longer recalls his time in the ${Material Plane}$ clearly.
import.label: Plains of Reflection

import.name: Ancient Promenade
import.description:
Recently explored triangular shaped building that seems to have always been one story tall and seems moderately well intact.

The barriers here were powerful and could inflict damage if not properly accessed. Particularly a set of ${Purple}$ barriers that seemed to possibly ${Curse}$ any who tried to cross without proper attunement.

Additionally, the locks present were quite difficult to pick and seemed to be on a timer of approximately ${2 Hours}$ between failed lockpick attempts. Though a ${Scrambled Color Grid}$ seemed to appear on the opposite side of the door as an override or access panel of some kind.

There appeared to be a side entrance as well as a main entrance and a storage room that still had quite a few items within.

Though ${Ash}$ suspects there is still part of this building that is unexplored...
import.label: Ancient Promenade

import.name: Ancient Promenade
import.description: Recently explored ruins of an ancient building that seems to have been some kind of cafe with everything above the first floor destroyed, a ${Green Barrier}$ protecting the front entrance and a ${Purple Barrier}$ protecting the open "roof".
import.note: Unfound crystalline generator in the basement (Investigation DC20)
import.label: Ancient Promenade

import.name: Ancient Temple-esq Building
import.description:
Having explored the temple, ${Quincy}$ feels very uneasy with regard to it and having communed with ${Dionysus}$, has determined that something should be done about it, but what is unclear.

The building appears resistant to magic and will lash out when seeming attacked, either with magical damage or cursing those who attack it.

${Abjuration}$, ${Necromantic}$, and some unknown magic seem to cover every part of the solid smooth stone that composes it.

The back annex also seems to have no entrance and attempting to simple ${Misty Step}$ into the back annex seems to fail and be quite painful.
import.note: Quincy was in here and felt strange because this is the location of the attempted ascension for Crane Vox as he was being detained for imprisonment, tainting the area.
import.label: Ancient Temple-esq Building

import.name: Ancient Castle Ruins
import.description:
Known to be the location of an important building in ancient times, the walls marked on the map no longer stand and the entire area appears to be particularly overgrown.

Exploring inside, you found no plants or vines above ground, noting several secret passages and a secret alchemy lab.

However, the top of the building was covered in thick root-like vines that seemed to be strangling the building and you heard occasional creaking throughout the halls as though the structure were shifting under a great weight.

In some places, the floors would give way and the place in general seemed dark and abandoned.

The last place to check a hidden staircase in a ${Guard Room}$...
import.label: Ancient Castle Ruins

import.name: Foothills of Anger
import.description: The area here seems to affect those that are here, driving them into a mild rage and occasionally driving the unprepared to strike out against others.
import.label: Foothills of Anger

import.name: Foot Prints heading North West
import.description: You found footprints here and attempted to follow them, later relying on ${Orla Jr. Jr.}$'s sense of smell to follow them further after the footprints disappeared, however the trail went cold a few miles northwest.
import.label: Foot Prints heading North West

import.description: Known to be a cave in the area.
import.note:
Findable Notes:
+ Has a cave entrance only visible between 5AM and 7AM
+ Otherwise requires swimming to access
+ Have until 7:30AM til the cave entrance is flooded again
+ Takes Approximately 10 minutes of walking and climbing to be safe, but there is a trap door and ladder down out of the cave and then back up to an adjacent, sealed off cave
+ Has a teleportation circle down one part of the cave.
+ Directions: Given as doorways for the one from which you're looking in a clockwise order.
    + Teleportation Circle:
        + 2, 3, 1, 2
    + Ritual Area:
        + 2, 1, 4, 3

    5. Rough Manmade Cave
        1. Stream

3. Natural Cave

Old kingdom, over-run by monsters ~150 years ago.

import.label: Green Pastures

import.name: Shadowfell
import.description:
A plane of existence overrun by death and decay. Dead trees and earth litter the surface, and it's known to be home to deep, immense, and swirling caves that hide dark and powerful creatures.

Rare and powerful enchanting and alchemical ingredients bring mighty champions from all over, leaving their findings and gear among the death and rott covering the surface here.

Some cities stand here, covered in the same darkness, fortified castles sheltering the occupants from the terrifying nightmares wandering the darkened plains here.
import.label: Shadowfell

import.name: Open Reykurax
import.description: This is merely a map link for players to open the map of Reykurax
import.label: Open Reykurax

import.name: Alisco's Tomb
import.description: Covered with an illussary buble that makes the area appear invisible, from the inside it is a lush open field with clouds and trees. The ground is a thick lush grass and entering can be overwhelming. An ornate solid marble entrance seems to cover a set of stairs that descend into the ground. The area outside the illusionary boundary shows wildlife and trees and clouds and such. Inside the tomb you found pedestals and ${Wraiths}$, learning the doors could be opened by putting ${Power Crystals}$ on the pedestals, but that more ${Wraiths}$ spawned when removing a crystal from a pedestal, and that the wraith that appeared next to eh pedestal had a shimmering aura of the color matching the crystal, each appearing to have unique properties. + Red: Explodes + Green: Poisonous Aura + ${@Blue}$: Hard to hit Reaching the back of the tomb, you found a room with a bed where a body seemed to be laid to rest with a powerful Golem protecting it. After reaching the end you managed to talk with ${Alisco}$, and managed to learn some things about the area and convinced him to let you take 2 items from his crypt, opting to take ${King's Guard Cloak}$ and ${Alisco's Song Book}$.
import.label: Alisco's Tomb

import.name: Path of Vengence
import.description:
A violent place shrouded in clouds and lightning.

When last you saw it, you watched as a giant hand descended through the clouds, smashing dozens of ${Lost Souls}$ into dust before is was dragged back into the shadowy mist.
import.label: Path of Vengence

import.name: Peum
import.description:
Peum is a religious city founded around the Church Caelillt, which has reside there for several centuries.

Over the last few decades it has grown quite a bit, many giving thanks to Ixeba Ratabu for its growth and his political sway to convince people to come.

Another is the beautiful Alucavous Esplanade, that offers a protected beautiful park to stroll through.

It's remote location and semi-isolationist stance on many political topics has made it an ideal refuge for those who wish to avoid the outside world. As a large provider of food to the Draconian empire, it is also well suited to feeding those refuges as well.
import.note:
This city also serves as the main perch for Cthulu in the world. While diminished from the apocalypse millennia ago, his followers have kept him strong here through rituals and sacrifice and a great deal of magical showmanship to hide it all.

---

This level park resides outside the Church Caelillt.

Constructed by the church's servants, the land is considered holy by the citizens.

alucinor (Dream:Common)
pravus (Evil:Common)

The land is actually desecrated but masked by strong magic (DC:30 to perceive, DC:30 for non-religion, DC:25 for religious).

While seemingly safe, many of the church's servants kidnap and kill innocents here as sacrifice to Cthulhu to keep his blessings.
import.label: Peum

import.name: Grappling Hook

import.label: Grappling Hook

import.label: The Hoffle

import.description: Overgrown with vines and weeds, this home seems in a particular state of decay...
import.label: Overgrown Home

import.name: Simple House
import.description: Fairly simple in its structure, this home seems mostly intact...
import.label: Simple House

import.name: Damaged House
import.description: This house has several large holes in its walls and seems to just barely be standing. Body parts litter the ground around it and aged blood seems to line its walls...
import.label: Damaged House

import.name: Food Storage Building
import.description: A storage building seeming to contain grains, vegetables, and other plant foods.
import.label: Food Storage Building

import.label: Farming Utility Storage

import.description: Bearing no particular denomination or god, this seems to be a place for any to come for worship or contemplation.
import.label: Makeshift Temple

import.name: Mysterious House
import.description:
Has runes along the base of the building. Using detect magic, there's no magic to the runes.

Inside you found 3 floors with Inn like rooms and walls covered in tiny spiders. Exploring, you stumbled across an invisible spider after closing yourself into a room with it, and found 2 corpses bludgeoned to death against a wall with magical rings on them.

On the top most floor you found a corpse, suspended in the hallway, various limbs missing with a note and several lettered tiles on it. A near-by room had a large hole in the ceiling and an extremely large spider could be seen slowly moving through the canopy.
import.note: In Graves End
import.label: Mysterious House

import.name: Carriage Shed
import.description:
With large exterior facing doors, this building was meant to contain a carriage or 2 along with a horse, and shelter them from the elements.

You found a mother and 2 children inside here on arrival, seemingly stuck after others from the settlement left in the last carriage, though those who ran died according to the mother. She and her children have been in hiding ever since, surviving on the food left in the shed and being as quiet as possible while waiting to be saved.
import.note: In Graves End
import.label: Carriage Shed

import.name: Mysterious Laboratory
import.description:
Searching the building, the only floor of interest seems to be the basement, the rest of the building almost eriely sterile and the floors seeming to exhibit some form of self cleaning.

In the basement, there seems to be a vault surrounded or encased in a bright white circular field with what seems to be at least 10 artifacts of some kind, a journal, a note, and a ${Silver Power Crystal}$ on a pedestal in the middle.

Looking at the vault, it seemed to have a panel in which tiles could be placed, with 4 tiles already in place:

```
      I _ _ _ _ _ _ _
_ _ _ _ T _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ L
   _ _ _ N _ _ _ _ _ _ _
```

Seemingly related to the riddle that was indicated by ${Emereta Ringa}$.
import.label: Mysterious Laboratory

import.name: Reykurax
import.description:
Filled with a thick fog, the souls of the dead reside here.

Only one city stands here, told to be in the center of the endless expanse of mist covered land, ${Stjornu}$.

Waking up in this realm can be overwhelming to the mind resulting in 2d10 ${Psychic}$ damage if no protections are taken to steady your mind.

The use of ${Divine}$ spells results in 6d10 ${Psychic}$ damage.
import.label: Reykurax

import.description: ${Opulence}$ is buried here after a trail of ${Magic Mouths}$.

import.description:
A large group of panthers reside in this area.

The seeming leader of the group took a ${Curellian Artifact}$ as payment for their passing and seemed intent on consuming the artifact and sharing it with his kin.

import.name: Brurniril Mountains
import.description:
A large mountain range in the area, it is largely unexplored.

It is suspected to have many caves that connect to the caves beneath ${Lake Ricrire}$, and that many of those also connect to the ${Lampi-Maejuri}$ strait of ${Lurus}$.
import.label: Brurniril Mountains

Notably, the ground here seemed to be perverted in some way, showing as Evil to the eyes of Clerics using ${Detect Good and Evil}$

Restaurant in Curell, known for its Fried Pressed Dough.

Near the better off part of Curell and popular among all the local citizens.

Semi big area, has an indoor and outdoor area and commonly find fancy pipe smoking around.

import.name: Warden Garrison
import.description:
A 3 story building with 10 floors underground for evidence storage, documents, and resting troops.

The 6<sup>th</sup> basement floor currently stores evidence for the disappearing people in ${Curell}$.
import.label: Warden Garrison

import.name: Assassination Attempt
import.description:
An assassin attempted to kill a woman here, ${Ginnet}$ and ${Eldith}$ managing to reach it in time to save her life with a ${Scroll of Revivify}$.

While in pursuit, ${Lucy}$ stumbled across a body being dragged into the bushes near by and found herself in a fight with some kind of invisible snake/lizard creature that she lost in the smoke of her ${Soul Mist Bomb}$. ${Ash}$, ${Quincy}$, and ${Erilore}$ arriving just in time to seemingly drive it off and resuscitate ${Lucy}$.
import.label: Assassination Attempt

import.name: Blind Spot
import.description:
A seeming blind spot in visibility as groups come around the corner. This seems to be getting used by the slaves to some small degree, possibly for an escape attempt of some kind?

You've seen several slaves killed in your time down here though, perhaps the attempt has already been foiled.
import.label: Blind Spot

import.name: Rust
import.description:
Due to its small size and the vast amount of ocean water around, many of the builds had issues with metal rusting quickly in the area, giving rise to the city's name while it was being built.

The instability of the island however made metal the prime candidate even with this as a factor, leading to some creative ways of preventing rust from forming.

At its height, while still suffering from rust issues, the city drew a number of tourists and its port served many boats from all the nations as an easy resting point between the seas.

This however, as a leoterran city,it  also made it an important tactical point, lead to its quick fall at the start of the war between ${Leoterra}$ and ${Nautregno}$.
import.label: Rust
